Reasoning: The paper deals with the performance analysis of Reed-Solomon codes over AWGN channels, which is a topic related to information theory (cs.IT) and communication theory (cs.COMM). The use of random mapping and the derivation of analytic bounds suggest a focus on network information theory (cs.NI) and signal processing (cs.SI). The simulation-based bounds and the comparison with other coding schemes suggest a focus on data structures and algorithms (cs.DS).
